name: $category
desc: Returns: The category of interval of values for continuous or ordinal observations conforming to this ObservationDefinition.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The category of interval of values for continuous or ordinal observations conforming to this ObservationDefinition.

name: $range
desc: Returns: The low and high values determining the interval. There may be only one of the two.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The low and high values determining the interval. There may be only one of the two.

name: $context
desc: Returns: Codes to indicate the health context the range applies to. For example, the normal or therapeutic range.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Codes to indicate the health context the range applies to. For example, the normal or therapeutic range.

name: $appliesTo
desc: Returns: Codes to indicate the target population this reference range applies to.

name: $addappliesTo
desc: Codes to indicate the target population this reference range applies to.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: Codes to indicate the target population this reference range applies to.

name: $gender
desc: Returns: Sex of the population the range applies to.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Sex of the population the range applies to.

name: $age
desc: Returns: The age at which this reference range is applicable. This is a neonatal age (e.g. number of weeks at term) if the meaning says so.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The age at which this reference range is applicable. This is a neonatal age (e.g. number of weeks at term) if the meaning says so.

name: $gestationalAge
desc: Returns: The gestational age to which this reference range is applicable, in the context of pregnancy.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The gestational age to which this reference range is applicable, in the context of pregnancy.

name: $condition
desc: Returns: Text based condition for which the reference range is valid.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Text based condition for which the reference range is valid.
